File: AFP/Wikus De Wet JOHANNESBURG -  The ANC has set up a Task Team to make recommendations to the NEC on the findings contained in the State Capture Report. The task team consists of Jeff Radebe who's the convener, Joel Netshitenzhe, Thoko Didiza, Ronald Lamola, Naledi Pandor and Lindiwe Maseko. READ: WATCH | ANC NWC briefs media Part three of the report, released earlier this week, details several dodgy dealings at Bosasa. Former President Jacob Zuma, ANC Chairperson Gwede Mantashe, and Party Campaign Head, Nomvula Mokonyane, have all been named in the report. The ANC maintains that the work of the State Capture Commission is vital to ensure such large scale corruption never happens again. Read the full statement below:  ANC Statement on Reports of Judicial Commission of Inquiry Into Allegations of State Capture by eNews Channel Africa on Scribd  Corruption was Bosasa’s way of doing business, according to part three of the State Capture report. It implicates top ANC members. The report says Bosasa was awarded government contracts worth at least R2.37-billion between 2000 and 2016. Politicians also benefited from this business with Bosasa. Reporter Heidi Giokos brings you more on this. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA